python-ligo-lw (2.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * don't write attributes to element start tags if set to their default values.  this is a small I/O savings.
  * change the Stream attribute "Encoding"'s default to "Text"
  * this change is not, strictly, correct, because this attribute's default value is different for different Type values, but since only Type="Local" is supported this change leads to behaviour that is compatible with the DTD and with written specifications and removes Encoding from documents when set to "Text", which is a small I/O savings.  the library no longer writes documents with Encoding set to "", but continues to interpret that value to mean "Text".

 -- Kipp Cannon <kipp@g.ecc.u-tokyo.ac.jp>  Thu, 22 May 2025 12:00:00 +0900

python-ligo-lw (2.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * improve ligolw_add garbage collection
  * drop support for python 2
  * drop support for python < 3.3
  * remove all deprecated symbols, all compatibility stubs
  * elimiate XML format flexibility:  array, table, param, time_slide, process, modules' requirements and features incorporated into element base classes
  * lsctables:  drop support for legacy ifos and instruments encodings
  * add missing metdata to segments.LigolwSegments:  .names, .instruments
  * many performance improvements in tokenizer C code
  * types.py:  add support for strings to ToNumPyType
  * LigolwSegments.coalesce():  also coalesce the lists
  * LigolwSegments:  set "valid" segments in .insert_from_segwizard() .insert_from_segmentlistdict()
  * move name-specific class instantiation plumbing from lsctables' and dbtables' content handlers to .__new__() methods of respective classes
  * with all of the above there is no longer a need for a custom content handler in standard use cases, so set a sensible default on load_fileobj() and remove all related code.
  * drop support for ilwd:char compatibility mode from remaining programs in bin/ (the API is now too different from glue's to continue using glue to provide that feature)
  * reorganize and flatten the namespace:  move package from ligo.lw to ligolw, move the ligolw.py module into __init__.py, import types, lsctables and utils subpackage into ligolw namespace --- common use case is now a single import statement
  * remove verbose parameter throughout library, replacing with logging library

 -- Kipp Cannon <kipp@g.ecc.u-tokyo.ac.jp>  Thu, 25 Apr 2025 12:00:00 +0900

